ragmented reception of Roman law into the nation states of Europe, and the relevance of 'dogmatic' Roman law as opposed to 'antiquarian' Roman law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aHumanism. 0aLawxPhilosophy. 0aLaw, Medieval. 4aLaw. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Rome.2bisacsh1 aBaston, Karen G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCairns, John W., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aCairns, John W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDecock, Wim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHepburn, Jasmin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIbbetson, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIttersum, Martine J. van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJakab, Éva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKarr, Susan Longfield, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaclean, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOsler, Douglas J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPlessis, Paul J. du, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrévost, Xavier, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRossi, Guido, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStolte, Bernard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWijffels, Alain, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311078045140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781474408868?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.c